Sentencas: Porous La0.6Sr0.4CO0.2Fe0.8O3 (LSCF) electrodes on anode support cells were infiltrated with AgNO3 solutions in citric acid and ethylene glycol.
Titulo: Silver infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Two types of solid oxide fuel cells with the LSCF-Ag cathode, Ni-YSZ/YSZ/LSCF-Ag and Ni-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95(GDC)/GDC/LSCF-Ag, were examined in a temperature range 530-730 degrees C under air oxidant and moist hydrogen fuel.
Titulo: Silver infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The infiltration of about 18wt.% Ag fine particles into LSCF resulted in the enhancement of the power density of about 50%.
Titulo: Silver infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of Ni-YSZ/YSZ/LSCF was enhanced from 0.16Wcm(-2) to 0.25Wcm(-2) at 630 degrees C by infiltration of AgNO3.
Titulo: Silver infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: No significant degradation of out-put power was observed for 150h at 0.7V and 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Silver infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Ni-GDC/GDC/LSCF-Ag cell showed the maximum power density of 0.415Wcm(-2) at 530 degrees C. (c) 2008
Titulo: Silver infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
